1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
Science has a clearer story about mirages than social media does.

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:07,200
Ever seen water on a hot road?

3
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:10,800
That’s a mirage, but it’s not what it seems.

4
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:16,000
Mirages happen due to light bending through layers of air with different temperatures.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,200
That’s called refraction!

6
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:21,600
It tricks our brains into seeing things that aren’t really there.

7
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:27,600
So when you think you see water, it’s actually an illusion shaped by the heat.

8
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:30,000
